Forgive the bard : ere long the offending paper will pay the penalty, for presuming to murmur against the mighty powers. The fires which it insulted will turn it into ashes, and the ashes will experience avenging waters. If the bard is to pay the penalty condign, Phoebus and the Muses make this request‚ that if Arthur is not to you what of old he was, you, Tilen, may condescend to be to him what you have been. ·
